To automatically generate a List of Figures in your LATEX document, you can use the following commands:

**Example:**

```
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{titletoc}
\usepackage{lipsum}
\usepackage{graphicx}

\begin{document}
\tableofcontents

\section{Introduction}
\lipsum[1]

\begin{figure}[ht]
\centering
\includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth]{example-image}
\caption{Example Figure}
\label{fig:example}
\end{figure}

\section{Methodology}
\lipsum[2]

\section{Results}
\lipsum[3]

\section{Conclusion}
\lipsum[4]

\listoffigures

\end{document}
```

**Output:**

```
Table of Contents

1. Introduction
2. Methodology
3. Results
4. Conclusion
5. List of Figures

List of Figures

1. Example Figure (Figure 1)
```

In this example, I added a figure with the label "Figure 1" and a caption "Example Figure". The command `\listoffigures` automatically generates a list of figures with the title "List of Figures" and includes the figure number and caption.

